ke Fourier analysis but for psychological salience. Trauma = high-amplitude narrow-band resonance. Personality = the shape of the spectrum. Emotion = total resonance energy. Habituation = amplitude decay. Cross-pollinates signal processing with psychology. Implementation: ~20 universal stimulus dimensions (threat, novelty, social-approval, loss, effort, etc.), person-specific weights, response = weighted activation sum with emotion label from dominant dimension. — Math: response(s) = Σ w_i * s_i * exp(-t/τ_i); emotion = argmax(|w_i * s_i|)",
